<paragraph id="6D0836D1130C5C52FF2DFB5CCC0EFA0E" blockId="8.[166,1225,1217,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">
Description. Head (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FE13FB5CCF73FB69" box="[485,614,1217,1244]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">figs 10, 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FD83FB5FCFD6FB69" box="[629,707,1217,1244]" captionStart="Figs 18–22" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[183,1215,425,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[174,1232,420,1749]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 18–22: 18–20. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., paratype: 18, 19 — female head; 20 — female terminalia proportionally:a—left bladeof hypogynium,b —spermathecae;c— proctigerwith cerci;d— ventralreceptacle. 21–22. Ophiomyia mukhorytsa sp. n., paratype: 21 — female head; 22 — female terminalia proportionally: a — left blade of hypogynium, b — spermathecae, c — proctiger with cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455730/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">18, 19</figureCitation>
). Orbit not projected above eye in profile, narrow, matt, without clear contour (anterior view); 2 orb s, 2 fr s; frorb sta sparse, reclinate; frons, orbits and ocellar triangle uniformly matt; frons with distinct dorsocentral suture; lunule rounded, with wide furrow from ptilinal fissure to facial carina; facial carina strongly projected above level of lunule, oval, in female 1.5× as wide as in male; ocellar triangle reaching to the level of upper fr s; maximum height of eye 7.5× maximum height of gena; vibrissal fasciculus long, gradually curved dorsally in male, long vibrissa presents in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130C5C52FF2DFA5FCE9FFA49" blockId="8.[166,1225,1217,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">
W i n g (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FEC2FA5CCC69FA69" box="[308,380,1473,1500]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">fig.17</figureCitation>
). Costa reaching M 
<subScript id="F1333494130C5C52FDAEFA49CF75FA57" attach="left" box="[600,608,1492,1506]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">1</subScript>
;last section of CuA 
<subScript id="F1333494130C5C52FCB6FA49CE5DFA57" attach="both" box="[832,840,1492,1506]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">1</subScript>
slightly shorter than penultimate; calypter grey, fringe and margin black. Length of wing 
<quantity id="AA4F9B34130C5C52FCDCFA7FCE93FA49" box="[810,902,1506,1532]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="461" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130C5C52FF2DF99FCDF9F9EE" blockId="8.[166,1225,1217,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">
Mesonotum black, shining, with golden undertone; scutulum the same, but undertone stronger (dorsal view); 2 dc; acr in 8–9 rows at level of 2 
<superScript id="9AC29B99130C5C52FC25F9BCCEF0F99A" attach="left" box="[979,997,1569,1583]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">nd</superScript>
dc; halter and legs black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130C5C52FF2DF9FFCE9BF889" blockId="8.[166,1225,1217,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">
M a l e g e n i t a l i a (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FE5BF9FCCF32F9C9" box="[429,551,1633,1660]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">figs12–16</figureCitation>
).Phallus typical for the genus, 
<quantity id="AA4F9B34130C5C52FC89F9FCCEF6F9C9" box="[895,995,1633,1660]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="461" unit="mm" value="0.35">0.35mm</quantity>
length.Distiphallus massive orbed anteriorly and more narrow triangular posteriorly (ventral view), distiphallus posteriorly distinctly longer than mesophallus (lateral view). Mesophallus slightly curved basally and rather long, 0.7× as long as distiphallus. Basiphallus with narrow sclerites (arms), 1.4× as long as distiphallus (ventral view) (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FD5CF97CCE3CF949" box="[682,809,1761,1788]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme moderately narrow (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FEE6F89CCC77F8A9" box="[272,354,1793,1820]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium elongated with narrow broadened arms and hypandrial apodeme abducted and slightly curved laterally as in 
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130C5C52FCE5F8BCCE9BF889" box="[787,910,1825,1852]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="461">figs 14, 15.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130D5C53FF15FF2DCE91FEFC" blockId="9.[174,1233,175,329]" pageId="9" pageNumber="462">
F e m a l e t e r m i n a l i a (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130D5C53FE0EFF32CF5DFF7F" box="[504,584,175,202]" captionStart="Figs 18–22" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[183,1215,425,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[174,1232,420,1749]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 18–22: 18–20. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., paratype: 18, 19 — female head; 20 — female terminalia proportionally:a—left bladeof hypogynium,b —spermathecae;c— proctigerwith cerci;d— ventralreceptacle. 21–22. Ophiomyia mukhorytsa sp. n., paratype: 21 — female head; 22 — female terminalia proportionally: a — left blade of hypogynium, b — spermathecae, c — proctiger with cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455730/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="462">fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Both spermatheca identical, dark brown, wider than high, its width 1.5× as maximum height; internal duct invagination scarcely visible, reaching the top of spermathecae; blade of hypogynium and proctiger with cerci of the same length; blade of hypogynium rounded apically, denticles of outer margin small, scarcely visible, directed apically, inner margin and membrane without scales.
</paragraph>
<caption id="39C86659130D5C53FF58F975CC6AF881" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="462" startId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" targetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130D5C53FF58F975CC6AF881" blockId="9.[174,1232,1768,1844]" pageId="9" pageNumber="462">
Figs 10–17. 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D52130D5C53FED2F974CF17F94B" authority="Guglya, 2020" authorityName="Guglya" authorityYear="2020" box="[292,514,1769,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kireshiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC3130D5C53FED2F974CF17F94B" box="[292,514,1769,1790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="462">Ophiomyia kireshiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="44F057B8130D5C53FDFCF975CF55F94B" box="[522,576,1768,1790]" pageId="9" pageNumber="462" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130E5C50FF2DFF32CF90FEDC" blockId="10.[166,1225,175,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">
Diagnosis. External morphology of the new species is similar to that of other 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D52130E5C50FF50FF52CC9CFF5C" box="[166,393,207,233]" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC3130E5C50FF50FF52CC3DFF5C" box="[166,296,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with fasciculus that cannot be reliably identificated without male dissection. The male terminalia are distinct in that the shape of phallus resenbles that of 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D52130E5C50FF50FE8DCCDDFE9C" authority="Cerny, 1994" authorityName="Cerny" authorityYear="1994" box="[166,456,271,298]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moravica">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC3130E5C50FF50FE8DCC21FE9C" box="[166,308,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">O. moravica</emphasis>
Černý, 1994
</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D52130E5C50FDEDFE8DCFBDFE9C" authorityName="Cerny" authorityYear="1994" box="[539,680,272,298]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moravica">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC3130E5C50FDEDFE8DCFBDFE9C" box="[539,680,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">O. moravica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a distinct gap between the mesophallus and the posterior half of the distiphallus (in lateral view), and the anterior part of the distiphallus 1.5× as long as the posterior.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130E5C50FF2DFEF2CC35FE1C" blockId="10.[166,1225,175,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">
The new species can be integrated to the Key of 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D52130E5C50FCFAFEF2CE9BFE3C" box="[780,910,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC3130E5C50FCFAFEF2CE9BFE3C" box="[780,910,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="15A07641130E5C50FC45FEF2C906FE3C" box="[947,1043,367,393]" name="Ukraine" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="09264B20130E5C50FBD5FEF2C9D4FE3F" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[1059,1217,367,394]" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" pagination="51 - 66" refId="ref19246" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2014. Mining flies of the genus Ophiomyia (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Eastern Ukraine and adjacent territories: Review of species without a fasciculus. Vestnik Zoologii, 48 (1), 51 - 66. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.2478 / vzoo- 2014 - 0005" type="journal article" year="2014">Guglya, 2014</bibRefCitation>
) as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D1130E5C50FF50FE52C9DCFD89" blockId="10.[166,1225,463,630]" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">
30a. Ocellar triangle large, reaching to the level of upper fr s; facial carina oval, without any invaginations or furrows (
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130E5C50FEBFFE71CC9FFDB7" box="[329,394,492,514]" captionStart="Figs 10–17" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[204,1217,370,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-78@9.[174,1217,344,1771]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 10–17. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., holotype: 10, 11 — male head; 12 — phallus (ventral view); 13 — phallus (lateral view); 14 — hypandrium (ventral view); 15 — hypandrium (lateral view); 16 — ejaculatory apodeme; 17 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455726/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F58C2A54130E5C50FE65FE71CCB8FDB7" box="[403,429,492,514]" captionStart="Figs 18–22" captionStartId="11.[174,213,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[183,1215,425,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[174,1232,420,1749]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 18–22: 18–20. Ophiomyia kireshiensis sp. n., paratype: 18, 19 — female head; 20 — female terminalia proportionally:a—left bladeof hypogynium,b —spermathecae;c— proctigerwith cerci;d— ventralreceptacle. 21–22. Ophiomyia mukhorytsa sp. n., paratype: 21 — female head; 22 — female terminalia proportionally: a — left blade of hypogynium, b — spermathecae, c — proctiger with cerci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455730/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">18</figureCitation>
). Distiphallus with massive orbed distal part and more narrow triangular proximal part (ventral view), that posteriorly distinctly longer that endophallus (lateral view) (
